TY  - JOUR
T1  - Using Information Technology to Add Value to Management Education
AU  - Alavi, Maryam
AU  - Yoo, Youngjin
AU  - Vogel, Douglas R.
Y1  - 1997/12/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/257035
DO  - 10.5465/257035
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1310
EP  - 1333
VL  - 40
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article describes the design and delivery of a graduate-level course in management at two universities via advanced information technology, which was used to enable collaborative learning, teaching with transcontinental student teams and multiple instructors, and integration of external expertise. This partnership enriched student learning and expedited faculty and institutional development. We predict that such transformations will increase as schools of management and institutions of higher learning in general seek to add educational value at low cost.
AB  - This article describes the design and delivery of a graduate-level course in management at two universities via advanced information technology, which was used to enable collaborative learning, teaching with transcontinental student teams and multiple instructors, and integration of external expertise. This partnership enriched student learning and expedited faculty and institutional development. We predict that such transformations will increase as schools of management and institutions of higher learning in general seek to add educational value at low cost.
